The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks for material-aware 3D shape analysis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the use of crowd-sourced data and mesh-aware conditional random fields, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions applications such as automatic texturing and physical simulation, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
